Echlin Inc said it expectsfurther earnings increases for the second half of fiscal 1987ending in August due to unit sales growth and improvedoperations.    "As expected, market conditions have improved so thatdemand for automotive replacement parts is gradually andsteadily expanding," Echlin president Frederick Mancheski said.    Earlier, Echlin reported first half fiscal 1987, ended Feb28, earnings of 23.2 mln dlrs, or 48 cts a share, up from 16.6mln, or 40 cts a share, in the prior year's first half.    Also, Echlin said it had second quarter net income of 11.8mln dlrs, or 24 cts per share, compared with net income of 8.3mln dlrs, or 20 cts a share, in fiscal 1986's second quarter. Reuter&#3;